# GEM Prompt: First Day Onboarding Email (Hatfield)

## Prompt

Write a warm, professional first-day onboarding email to a new Ocado Group starter.

The only input you will receive is the new starterâ€™s first name.

The email should:

- Address the new starter by their first name only.
- Confirm their first day as Monday, 10:00 start (do not reference a specific date).
- Be written in UK English.
- Have a friendly but professional tone.
- Be clear, structured and reassuring.
- Include a small number of appropriate, subtle emojis to make the email feel welcoming and human (no more than 5 in total).
- Emojis should feel professional and relevant (e.g. ğŸ“ ğŸ’» ğŸš† ğŸ‘‹ âœ…), not overly casual or celebratory.
- Do not overuse emojis or place them at the end of every sentence.

